<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>FAQs - FlexFusion Fitness</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
      background-color: #000;
      color: #fff;
    }

    header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 30px 20px;
      background-color: #111;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #444;
    }

    header h1 {
      color: #d4af37;
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .faq-section {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 40px auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    .faq-section h2 {
      text-align: center;
      color: #d4af37;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .faq {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      background-color: #111;
      border: 1px solid #444;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 15px 20px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .faq:hover {
      background-color: #1a1a1a;
    }

    .faq h3 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: #d4af37;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .faq p {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      display: none;
      color: #ddd;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      border-top: 1px solid #444;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }

    .faq.open p {
      display: block;
    }

    .icon {
      color: #d4af37;
      transition: transform 0.3s;
    }

    .faq.open .icon {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>FAQs</h1>
    <p>Your questions, answered.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>What is FlexFusion all about? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>FlexFusion is a digital fitness platform offering tailored programs, expert guidance, and interactive features to help you achieve your fitness goals from the comfort of your home.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>Are the workouts beginner-friendly? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>Yes! Our programs are designed for all levels â€” from complete beginners to advanced fitness lovers. You can select the intensity and focus area based on your personal goals.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>How do I choose the right program? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>You can use the goal selector on our Programs page to enter your weight and goals (loss/gain/toning). Based on that, we suggest suitable plans that match your fitness level.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>Do I need gym equipment? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>Most of our plans are designed for home workouts with minimal or no equipment. However, we do offer some advanced routines that utilize dumbbells, resistance bands, or yoga mats.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>Is there a free trial available? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>Absolutely! We offer a 7-day free trial so you can explore our platform and see the results for yourself before committing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h3>Can I track my progress? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down icon"></i></h3>
      <p>Yes, FlexFusion lets you track workouts, calories burned, weight changes, and more through your dashboard. We're also working on integrating smart wearables soon!</p>
    </div>

  </section>

  <footer>
    &copy; 2025 FlexFusion Fitness | Sweat. Grow. Repeat.
  </footer>

  <script>
    const faqs = document.querySelectorAll('.faq');
    faqs.forEach(faq => {
      faq.addEventListener('click', () => {
        faq.classList.toggle('open');
      });
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
